    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> February 2026</p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>[Your App Name]</strong> handles information. Our primary goal is to provide a functional alarm clock utility without compromising your privacy.</p>

    <h2>1. Data Collection</h2>
    <p>We do not collect, store, or share any personal information. This app does not require a user account, email address, or any form of registration to function.</p>

    <h2>2. Permissions and Usage</h2>
    <p>To provide its core functionality (waking you up with math problems), the app requires the following permissions on your device:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Alarms & Reminders:</strong> To schedule and trigger the alarm at your requested time.</li>
        <li><strong>Vibration:</strong> To provide physical alerts when the alarm sounds.</li>
        <li><strong>Full Screen Intent:</strong> To display the math puzzle over the lock screen so the alarm can be dismissed.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These permissions are used <strong>locally</strong> on your device. We do not use them to access your location, contacts, or files.</p>

    <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>This app operates entirely offline for its core features. We do not use third-party analytics, advertising networks, or cloud storage providers. No data is transmitted from your device to our servers or any third-party servers.</p>

    <h2>4. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>Because we do not collect any personal data, this app is safe for users of all ages and complies with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).</p>

    <h2>5. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date.</p>

    <div class="footer">
        <p><strong>Contact Us</strong></p>
